article.headline: Fordham 27, Columbia 10
article.story: NEW YORK (AP) -- Xavier Martin ran for 157 yards and three touchdowns to lead Fordham to a 27-10 victory over Columbia on Saturday night. The Rams (2-1) led 17-0 before John Rocholl kicked a 49-yard field goal for the Lions (0-1) as time ran out in the first half. Martin had a 14-yard touchdown run at 3:08 of the first quarter and his 51-yarder was his longest run of the game. Martin's 4-yard TD and Adam Danko's 32-yard field goal game the Rams a 27-3 lead at 4:30 of the third. Craig Hormann's 7-yard pass to Austin Knowlin at 1:37 of the final quarter was Columbia's only touchdown.
